❗️The State Power Committee held a round table with discussion panels in Poltava - "Participation of local self-government bodies in international territorial cooperation within the framework of the process of accession to the European Union" and "The Institute of Starostas and its influence on the functioning of communities". Using the example of territorial communities of Poltava Oblast, Sumy Oblast, Kharkiv Oblast's experience in the spheres of international territorial cooperation and the functioning of the Institute of Elders was considered, as well as the prospects for development were discussed. In particular, the participants of the event got acquainted with information about:

- draft of the Law of Ukraine "On International Territorial Cooperation" (#9450); - experience and geography of international cooperation of territorial communities of Ukraine (Poltava Oblast, Sumy Oblast, Kharkiv Oblast);
- Cities4Cities United4Ukraine initiative;
- the planning and financing system within the EU cohesion policy;
- cooperation of the territorial community of Poltava with international partners;
- involvement of international aid by communities of Sumy Oblast. 📲 Details
